
The release 1.0 (Cherimoya) of Flora-2 fixes a number of bugs and features
many improvements/changes in the syntax of the language, which make it even
more convenient for knowledge representation. This release includes a
self-contained Windows installer and a self-contained archive for
installing Flora-2 under Linux, Mac, and other Unixes.

The archive flora2bundle.tar.gz is for Linux/Mac/Cygwin users.
The installer flora2bundle.exe is for Windows users.

Details can be found in the release notes at
http://flora.sourceforge.net/release_notes.html
and the installation instructions at
http://flora.sourceforge.net/installation.html
